cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language tasks such as dialogue generation and evaluates the language coverage and generalization abilities of continuous sentence embeddings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new embedding method and evaluates the performance of existing methods for language tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for continuous sentence embeddings and evaluates their ability to learn structures of language. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses RNNs for continuous sentence embeddings. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper generates a large-scale dataset of sentences related to the content of realistic 3D indoor scenes.
